Client Hints can be accessed via JavaScript using the `navigator.userAgentData` API. For example, a website can retrieve Client Hints values like this:
javascript
if ('userAgentData' in navigator) {
  const hints = await navigator.userAgentData.getHighEntropyValues(['model', 'platform']);
  console.log(hints.model, hints.platform);
}

Research has shown that many websites use this method to collect Client Hints for tracking and advertising, raising privacy concerns about the protocol's implementation.
